    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-09-06T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-09-06T10:00:00-05:00" n="217"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d217">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">357.AB/9–551: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in India</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d217fn1">Repeated as telegram 266 to Karachi and 124 to New
                        York.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-09-06T11:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 6, 1951—11 a. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>524. Re Kashmir (<gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> 852, Sept 5):</p>
                <p>Dept agrees your comment wld be advisable for Graham leave when he once becomes
                    convinced there is nothing more to be accomplished in subcontinent. However, in
                    view Ind–<gloss target="#t_Pak1">Pak</gloss> comments Dixon left before
                    exhausting all possibilities, we consider advisable Graham not depart until sure
                    adequate time has elapsed without hopeful responses after submission his
                    proposals to <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss>–<gloss target="#t_GOP1"
                        >GOP</gloss>. If Graham asks your opinion this regard, you shld express this
                    view while making clear US not attempting influence him re decision.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d217fn2">
                        <p>The following comment was added in telegram 538, to New Delhi, September
                            6, repeated as telegram 270, to Karachi:</p>
                        <p>“Further <gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> 852, Sep 5, we believe
                            that report Graham contemplates filing might be ‘interim’ in nature to
                            prevent further freezing of situation. You might discreetly convey this
                            thought to him.</p>
                        <p>“<gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss> we are desirous that Graham consult
                            in NY before making report to <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>.”
                            (357.AB/9–551)</p>
                    </note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
